<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I have a simple form with a display group.</p>

<p>When trying to render the group separately in the view script, eg. &lt;?php echo $this-&gt;form-&gt;myGroup ?&gt;, the group is rendered without a fieldset although such decorator exists.</p>

<p>When rendering with &lt;?php echo $this-&gt;form-&gt;myGroup-&gt;render($this) ?&gt;, the fieldset is added as expected.</p>

<p>I tracked this down to the getView() method of Zend_Form_DisplayGroup. It seems like this method simply returns $this-&gt;_view, unlike other getView() methods that use the viewRenderer helper to return the default view.</p>

